wxWidgets docs: wxCalendarEvent

.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBwxCalendar() :: #wxCalendar{}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBwxCalendarEvent() :: wx:wx_object().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBwxCalendarEventType() ::\fR
\fB          calendar_sel_changed | calendar_day_changed |\fR
\fB          calendar_month_changed | calendar_year_changed |\fR
\fB          calendar_doubleclicked | calendar_weekday_clicked.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBgetDate(This) -> wx:wx_datetime() when This :: wxCalendarEvent().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the date.


.RE
.B
\fBgetWeekDay(This) -> wx:wx_enum() when This :: wxCalendarEvent().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the week day on which the user clicked in \fIEVT\\_CALENDAR\\_WEEKDAY\\_CLICKED\fR handler.

.PP
It doesn't make sense to call this function in other handlers.


.RE
